description.narrative: 1. GARDP’s antimicrobial exploratory, evaluation and development programme sets out to build a long-term portfolio of therapeutic interventions necessary to address the unavoidable development of resistance to any novel compound brought to patients and recover and share experts´ knowledge to speed up AMR drug discovery. 2. GARDP’s neonatal sepsis programme aims to develop new antibiotic treatments and provide an evidence base for the use of antibiotics, both old and new, in neonates with confirmed or suspected sepsis. 3. GARDP’s paediatric antibiotics programme aims to expedite the development of new, improved and adapted antibiotics to treat serious bacterial infections in children of all ages. The programme aims to develop antibiotics for countries with a high burden of drug-resistance – for use in hospitals and the community – in both LMIC and high-income settings. 4. GARDP’s STI programme aims to develop and register a new, affordable treatment for gonorrhoea, that works on multidrug-resistant cases and will support the integration of a new treatment into current STI management by investigating antibiotic combinations.
GARDP’s mission is to develop and deliver new treatments for bacterial infections where drug resistance is present or emerging or for which inadequate treatment exists.
